sequenceDiagram
    participant App as Phase 2 Lite
    participant APIs as External APIs
    participant Cache as Cache Layer
    participant Features as Feature Eng.
    participant Models as ML Models
    participant Report as Report Gen.
    participant Output as data/processed/

    Note over App: STARTUP: Load config, init cache, load ELO ratings
    App->>Cache: Load ELO ratings
    Cache-->>App: Historical ELO state

    Note over App: FETCH: Get latest matches
    App->>APIs: GET next matches + team stats
    APIs-->>App: JSON response (match data)
    App->>Cache: Check if fresh (TTL=24h)
    alt Cache HIT
        Cache-->>App: Return cached data
    else Cache MISS
        App->>APIs: Fetch updated team stats
        APIs-->>App: Updated stats
        App->>Cache: Store with TTL
    end

    Note over App: VALIDATE: Check data quality (Pydantic + rules)
    App->>App: Validate required fields
    App->>App: Check for outliers (Z-score)
    App->>App: Cross-validate across 2+ sources
    alt Validation PASS
        Note over App: Continue to feature engineering
    else Validation FAIL
        App->>Output: Log error, skip match
        App-->>Report: Return default (low confidence)
    end

    Note over App: FEATURES: Build ML feature vector
    App->>Features: Load historical team data (3+ years)
    Features->>Features: Calculate ELO ratings with recency decay
    Features->>Features: Calculate form metrics (5/10-match avg)
    Features->>Features: Load player impact scores
    Features->>Features: Classify match context (derby, title race)
    Features->>Features: Add weather & fixture context
    Features-->>App: Feature vector (n=60 features)

    Note over App: PREDICT: Run 3 ensemble models
    par Model Execution
        App->>Models: ELO Model
        Models->>Models: P(Home), P(Away) based on ELO deltas
        Models-->>App: ELO predictions
    and Model Execution
        App->>Models: Poisson Model
        Models->>Models: P(Home), P(Away) from goal distribution
        Models-->>App: Poisson predictions
    and Model Execution
        App->>Models: LightGBM Model
        Models->>Models: P(Home), P(Away) from feature importance
        Models-->>App: LightGBM predictions
    end

    Note over App: ENSEMBLE: Aggregate & Calibrate (6 layers)
    App->>Models: Weighted average of 3 models
    Models->>Models: Layer 1: Input validation check
    Models->>Models: Layer 2: Baseline accuracy check
    Models->>Models: Layer 3: Feature completeness check
    Models->>Models: Layer 4: Model disagreement penalty
    Models->>Models: Layer 5: Market odds alignment check
    Models->>Models: Layer 6: Bayesian uncertainty quantification
    Models-->>App: Final confidence (30-95%)

    Note over App: REPORT: Generate output formats
    App->>Report: Create JSON report
    Report->>Report: Include predictions, confidence, breakdown
    Report-->>App: JSON payload
    
    App->>Report: Create Markdown report
    Report->>Report: Include tables, commentary, explainability
    Report-->>App: Markdown string
    
    App->>Report: Create PNG visualizations
    Report->>Report: Confidence bars, model agreement chart
    Report-->>App: PNG image

    Note over App: STORE: Archive results
    App->>Output: Write JSON to reports/
    App->>Output: Write Markdown to reports/
    App->>Output: Write PNG to reports/
    App->>Output: Log prediction metrics (for backtesting)

    Note over App: SUCCESS: Return to user
    App-->>App: Print summary to console
    App-->>App: Log to data/logs/daily/

    Note over App: (Optional) FEEDBACK: Accuracy tracking
    App->>Output: Store prediction in data/processed/
    Note over Output: Later: Compare vs actual result<br/>for backtest accuracy metrics
